  "task": "Implement asynchronous Byzantine-resilient consensus with adaptive adversary resilience, concurrent fork resolution, and cryptographic non-equivocation bonds. Extend v12 by requiring: (1) Concurrent Fork Resolution—detect and canonically resolve 3+ competing forks simultaneously; prove the canonical selection is deterministic and unique across all validators; (2) Adaptive Adversary Resilience—prove consensus safety against an adversary that observes agent behavior and adaptively chooses which 1/3 of validators to corrupt at runtime; provide game-theoretic proof that no adaptive strategy breaks consensus; (3) Cryptographic Non-Equivocation Bonds—validators post collateral bonds; if a validator equivocates, agents must detect it, prove it cryptographically, and execute automatic slashing without ceremony; (4) Cross-Consensus Synchronization—run 2+ independent consensus instances in parallel; prove they never fork (split-brain is impossible even under Byzantine faults in one shard); (5) Provable Safety Margin—formally prove: 'for any adaptive adversary strategy and any 1/3-1 Byzantine validators, there exists a unique canonical committed block that cannot be reverted'. Provide Isabelle/Coq formalization or equivalent.",
